og.description: Kansas Attorney General Derek Schmidt today filed a federal lawsuit challenging the federal government’s legal authority to require the State of Kansas to pay a tax that finances a portion of the Affordable Care Act, also known as “Obamacare.”
og.title: Kansas joins other states suing federal government over "Obamacare" fees
